# Electron UI Tokens Convention

- Keep design tokens centralized in dedicated files (for example `styles/tokens.css` or `theme/tokens.ts`); avoid scattered per-page constants.
- Use explicit semantic token names; avoid ambiguous abbreviations like `sm1`, `color2`, `gapA`.
- Group tokens by concern (spacing, radius, color, typography, z-index, motion) and keep each file focused on one concern.
- Prefer CSS variables or typed theme objects for shared values; avoid hard-coded values repeated in JSX.
- Keep component-specific overrides near component files, but source values from shared tokens.
- Remove legacy token aliases after call sites are migrated; do not leave stale fallback names.

## Example

```text
BAD: margin: 13px; border-radius: 7px repeated in multiple pages.
GOOD: use shared tokens like --spacing-small and --radius-card across components.
```
